<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - CHASSIS ACCESSORIES - TROUBLESHOOTING - Two
        Speed Axle With Manual or Allison Non-Electronic Automatic Transmission
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Two Speed Axle With Manual or Allison Non-Electronic Automatic Transmission</title>
        <table id="t0823904" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Two Speed Axle With Manual or Allison Non-Electronic Automatic Transmission</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.61in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.57in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.67in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.84in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.35in"/>
                <thead valign="bottom">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>When equipped with a International engine, does two speed axle shift but speedometer
                                does not reflect correct speed and mileage?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 3.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect ECM conn. (379). Turn key on and with two speed switch in low position and
                                then high position, measure voltage from circuit 93A, pin 28, to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(379), 93A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts in low, 0 volts in high position.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Refer to Engine Diag- nostic Manual for trouble- shoot- ing the ECM.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 93A or dash conn. (2), then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check fuse F14 for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F14</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At fuse F14, cavity A, measure voltage from circuit 12A to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F14, cav. A, 12A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Re- install fuse. Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 12A, then repair. Re-install fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect dash conn. (13). Turn key on and with two speed switch in high position,
                                measure voltage from circuit 93C, cavity K1, to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(13), 93C, cav. K1, to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 11.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With two speed switch in low position and at (13), measure voltage from circuit 93B,
                                cavity K2, to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(13), 93B, cav. K2, to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 11.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (13). Disconnect electric shift motor conn. (703) with electric shift,
                                or air shift solenoid conn. (263). Is axle equipped with an electric shift motor?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 10.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (703), measure resistance of white wire to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(703), white wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in white wire, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At shift motor conn. (703) measure voltage from brown wire to ground with axle switch
                                in low position.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(703), brown wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace shift motor.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in brown wire, then repair. If condition persists,
                                go to next step.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At electric shift motor (703) or air shift solenoid conn. (263), measure voltage from
                                red wire to ground with two speed axle switch in high position.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(703) or (263), red wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace electric shift motor or air shift solenoid.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in red wire, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At (13), install jumper wires from circuit 93C, cav. K1 to ground and from circuit
                                93B, cav. K2 to ground. At cab harness end of two speed axle conn. (14), measure
                                resistance of circuit 93C, cav. C, to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(14), 93C to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 93C, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>If axle is equipped with an air shift solenoid, go to next step. At (14), measure
                                resistance of circuit 93B, cav. B, to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(14), 93B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 93B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At two speed axle harness side of conn. (14), and with two speed switch in low
                                position, measure resistance from M1BLUE wire, cavity A, to M1BROWN wire, cavity B.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(14), M1 BLUE cav. A to M1 BROWN cav. B.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in M1BLUE or M1BROWN wire, [also conn. (59) with manual
                                trans.] or two speed axle switch, then repair. If none found, replace two speed axle
                                switch.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With two speed switch in high position, measure resistance from M1BLUE wire, cavity A,
                                to M1RED wire, cavity C.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(14), M1 BLUE cav. A to M1 RED cav. C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in M1RED wire, [also conn. (59) with manual trans.] or
                                two speed axle switch, then repair. If none found, replace two speed axle switch.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove jumper wires and reconnect connectors. Two speed axle shift circuits check
                                good.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
